There’s nothing like a bit of sun to get you in the mood for a drink, eh? With temperatures reaching balmy highs of around 18 degrees this week, it’s the perfect time to host the first barbeques of the year. Whether it’s a full-blown get together or a few quiet drinks in the garden with your girls, nothing calls for cocktails quite like the early signs of a warm summer – and this berry margarita recipe is the perfect tipple for the mood. Josiah Carter, a reality TV personality and mixologist, has shared his favourite spring cocktail recipe below – so you can make it at home. The berry margarita is a delicious, fruity twist on the classic margarita – the perfect cocktail for warming up to the summer months. To make this you’ll need a cocktail shaker, strainer, a small tumbler glass and a lighter. Ingredients       Method To dazzle with the garnish, Josiah says: ‘Simply cut a piece of skin off an orange and hold an open flame, such as a lighter, to it for a couple of seconds. ‘As the rind begins to burn, squeeze the orange and you should get some flames. ‘Then, pop it in the drink and you’re good to go.’ Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk. MORE : A Polish bar in London is serving a Ukrainian cocktail to raise money for charity MORE : Three caffeinated cocktails to try this International Coffee Day MORE : Bullshot recipe: How to make the unusual cocktail that features beef broth and vodka